# Context hygiene

This project burns context mainly via large `StrReplace`/`Write` history. Follow these every turn.
Read/search/shell trimming lives in `token-economy` — keep that rule for those habits.

## Edits

- Prefer **small** `StrReplace` (ideally under ~500 tokens / ~2KB of `new_string`).
- Do **not** `Write` an existing file’s full body — patch with `StrReplace`.
- `Write` only for **new** files, or when the user explicitly asks to replace the whole file.
- Avoid re-editing the same hot file dozens of times in one chat; finish the change, then move on.
- Batch `README.md` / `GOALS.md` updates **once at the end** of a feature task (see auto-documentation rule).

## Chat lifecycle

- For a **new workstream** (new feature, unrelated bug, post-audit follow-up), tell the user to **start a new chat** and point at the relevant files/plan — do not keep stacking history here.

## Do not optimize

- Unused Cursor tool definitions and skill *descriptions* are fixed overhead — ignore them.
